What is OOP?
	OOP stand Object Oriented Programming. In OOP, we write a program by using class and object. OOP provide the facility of reusability.
What is Class?
		Class are a blueprint, Skelton, or Template to build a specific type of object. In other word, we can say that class is a user define data type. A class contain data member and member function. The behavior of class by default is private.
Coding Example. 
Class person
{
// Data member.
//Member function
}
What is Object?
	Object is an instant of a class. 

How many Pillars of OOP. 
		Pillars of OOP are four. 
1.	Abstraction
2.	Encapsulation
3.	Inheritance
4.	Polymorphism
